HEADWORD: Gauffering
<hw>Gauf"fer*ing</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A mode of
plaiting or fluting.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Gauffering iron</b></col>, <cd>a kind of fluting iron for
fabrics.</cd> -- <col><b>Gauffering press</b></col> <fld>(Flower
Manuf.)</fld>, <cd>a press for crimping the leaves and petals into
shape.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gauffre</ent>⟦br⟧
